# Wikipefia MDX Content Authoring

## Frontmatter (Required)

Every `.mdx` file must start with YAML frontmatter. The `slug` field must match the filename (without `.mdx`).

```yaml
---
title:
  ru: "Заголовок"
  en: "Title"
  cz: "Název"
slug: "article-slug" # must match filename
author: "teacher-slug" # optional
keywords:
  ru: ["ключевое слово"]
  en: ["keyword"]
  cz: ["klíčové slovo"]
created: "2025-01-01" # ISO date, required
updated: "2025-06-01" # optional
difficulty: "beginner" # optional: beginner | intermediate | advanced
estimatedReadTime: 10 # optional: minutes
prerequisites: # optional: other article slugs in this subject
  - "introduction"
tutors: # optional: teacher slugs
  - "ivan-petrov"
---
```

**Required fields**: `title`, `slug`, `keywords`, `created`. All `LocalizedString` and `LocalizedKeywords` fields must include all three locales: `ru`, `en`, `cz`.

## Front Pages (`_front.mdx`)

Every locale directory must have `_front.mdx` with `slug: "_front"`. This renders as the subject's main page. It should contain: course overview, why the subject matters, course structure outline, prerequisites, and instructor info.

## Available MDX Components

```mdx
<Callout type="info|warning|error">Content here</Callout>

<Tabs>
  <Tab label="Tab 1">Content</Tab>
  <Tab label="Tab 2">Content</Tab>
</Tabs>

<Quiz>
  <Question text="Question?">
    <Option value="a">Wrong</Option>
    <Option value="b" correct>
      Correct
    </Option>
  </Question>
</Quiz>

<CodePlayground language="python">print("editable code")</CodePlayground>

<Collapse title="Click to expand">Hidden content</Collapse>

<MathBlock>\text{Displayed equation: } E = mc^2</MathBlock>

<Figure src="/assets/image.svg" alt="description" caption="Caption text" />
```

## Math

- Inline: `$E = mc^2$`
- Block: `$$\sum_{i=1}^{n} i = \frac{n(n+1)}{2}$$`

## Localization

- Articles don't need to exist in every locale — site falls back: requested → `en` → `ru`
- All frontmatter strings (`title`, `keywords`) must include all 3 locales regardless
- Write each locale's content in its native language, not machine-translated placeholders

## Content Quality

- Start with a clear `# Heading` matching the article title
- Use progressive disclosure: fundamentals first, details in `<Collapse>` blocks
- Include working code examples with comments
- Use `<Callout type="warning">` for common mistakes
- Use `<Callout type="info">` for tips and cross-references to other articles
- Link to related articles: `[Core Concepts](/subject-slug/core-concepts)`
